age-private classes, but my class is public. I'm pondering whether a user-code filter is necessary—maybe not. I could update the build to run with add-opens, but it's already a native build. The test task doesn't include any jvmArgs except for the opened ones. But I wonder: is CGLIB even needed here? The existing ReflectUtils test does exclude that one case.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Exploring Java class loading**\\n\\nI’m looking at how `java.lang.ClassLoader` operates, especially within Spring patched versions that utilize lookup. That seems like a good direction to explore. Now, I should think about pulling some source context examples. Maybe I can search for upstream tests related to Enhancer, to see what other information I can find there. It's always interesting to uncover how dependencies and configurations interrelate!\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_397CfgGnNModPoLy9SqE906J|fc_0dbc26bbbbc8c673016a25a415a6348196827e07d90a3fc34f", "name": "bash", "arguments": {"command": "rg \"Enhancer\" local_repositories/source_context/org.springframework/spring-core/5.3.15/main/extracted -g '*Test*.java' || true"}}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "oca/gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 2043, "output": 2156, "cacheRead": 25600, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 29799, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "toolUse", "timestamp": 1780851668524, "responseId": "resp_0dbc26bbbbc8c673016a25a3d4ff708196b4cde7da8aaea03b"}}
