[recv] {"type": "turn_end", "message": {"role": "assistant", "content": [{"type": "thinking", "thinking": "**Considering CGLIB limitations**\n\nI think CGLIB might not be able to subclass package-private classes, but my class is public. I'm pondering whether a user-code filter is necessary—maybe not. I could update the build to run with add-opens, but it's already a native build. The test task doesn't include any jvmArgs except for the opened ones. But I wonder: is CGLIB even needed here? The existing ReflectUtils test does exclude that one case.\n\n**Exploring Java class loading**\n\nI’m looking at how `java.lang.ClassLoader` operates, especially within Spring patched versions that utilize lookup. That seems like a good direction to explore. Now, I should think about pulling some source context examples. Maybe I can search for upstream tests related to Enhancer, to see what other information I can find there. It's always interesting to uncover how dependencies and configurations interrelate!", "thinkingSignature": "{\"id\":\"rs_0dbc26bbbbc8c673016a25a3d5c80481969b11061eb47c7334\",\"type\":\"reasoning\",\"content\":[],\"encrypted_content\":\"gAAAAABqJaQV7QN10pfsFKM1xSvwA-STO6mXJOcWKy6R55ofKdHW3EnRvwIwiQvmb89XBJA1DHbP1XFvA7tMLEIVUIcipa12SeSTa4mMfq9xDGd2id5OU9NNBIad6YyLUr0xxR75WPx13IdeDb4u1aM7dyPKIn0MtP5an9bBeuRrIs5XoiYr2ni_vzrDRsHtJ3eTktYa5ipgkzalmMi4RZBG7_Z0K2B9CXyYcDsB_9J0xeND1jhexTZBGCeKDTgNUE5sOhV0K7gs19WIcQr-bGuRP7X0xA6DnqqT0PRpB4-TWMf2xmJkGdvab4BGIC8roWMhz5XEn1lwK71XfNasBNEibRpcVV8fov7j6mMqzi01ZYI92IdbiuqLF7vnqnZmXOMW-c8zIZRZCoEtZD30MjggHre0ByTC8IqUosZXsGbUVKTbIUCR409DJrWvVRjQYCetznEqJRgbyxcGv8dX0NItfgqxxKXwMZ1-m6tmRCzjYryCpjDX3aSPMCqv_fJ0lCUEAXYrL3h-Q4Rsdpqnt0UG_RYN4dDgu5afuEyd1PSUKXCf15lWZL_2Cg_OgAMHnhBhyYf8e71pkPe5eVfNfKSqf46BXVS0j3XXR-sPbl2HEm5eHkq5QgbvBl1qx4xYkeGC3NuA7dFl9XDW8i0lzaiAiOz2wCefC3qrP5Xr555bYsxpL_2YzgXLNMqPc0A45XJ2VQy-A76_AF6rDMN2DH9wolXDWxn1f7zf-SCjAYp_elJJ84DXqBPbI3TTFYm2tg_InUKjv0-e54qjVuFFNdOGaGS7XdedE2-mdDCcqbxpy9cUcP_m4LA_HYQy-cwZndXRC2uE